modules.description: This module tracks elapsed time in nanoseconds using `elapsed_ns` and optionally provides the system's time measurement period with `period_ns`. It operates directly on system time sources without requiring specific data structures. Use it for precise timing measurements in performance-critical sections of code or benchmarking.

This module tracks and advances a simulated monotonic time value. It provides `tick` to increment the time by one nanosecond and `tick_for` to increment by a specified number of nanoseconds. Directly used in testing time-dependent logic where precise control over time progression is required.
